  "title": "Systems Engineer (VMware)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Install, configure and manage VMware vSphere environments</li><li>Knowledge or experience of VMware NSX/NSX-T</li><li>Install, configure and maintain VM and VM template lifecycle</li><li>Work on Incidents, Service Requests/Change Requests and Root Cause Analysis</li><li>Work on migrations and upgrades/downgrades</li><li>Improve ways of working by scripting repetitive and mundane tasks</li><li>Open to learn and use automation using PowerShell/PowerCLI and Bash</li></ul><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Key requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>VMware vCenter</li><li>VMware ESXi</li><li>Windows Server</li><li>PowerShell/PowerCLI</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in computer science or related field.</li><li>At least 6 years’ relevant experience preferably in a Finance Institution.</li><li>Analytical thinking, problem solver, team player.</li></ul>",
